<headline>Flood Advisory issued April 30 at 12:03PM AST  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM AST THIS AFTERNOON...
* WHAT...Minor flooding caused by excessive periods of moderate to
heavy rainfall is expected.
* WHERE...A portion of Virgin Islands, including the following ,
Saint Croix and Saint Thomas.
* WHEN...Until 200 PM AST.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 1203 PM AST, Doppler radar indicated isolated
thunderstorms with strong showers in and around the islands.
Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the
advisory area.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood</description>
<instruction>Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.
Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.</instruction>
